The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 UGC raps solidarity

 New Delhi, Sept. 17: The University Grants Commission has rapped Delhi University teachers who went on a one-day strike on August 1 in support of Honda workers lathicharged by the police outside the factory in Gurgaon, reports our correspondent.

 The UGC has written to principals of Delhi University-affiliated colleges directing them to withhold a days salary of teachers who had gone on strike in support of the Honda workers and had demanded their release from police custody.

 The letter dated September 1, 2005, has been sent just a day after the Delhi University Teachers Association elections, which were won by the Left-backed Democratic Teachers Front.

 Duta has decided to hold a demonstration at the UGC office on September 21 to protest the dictatorship. Everyone has a right to protest, said former Duta president Vijender Sharma.




